**who —** The Guru — the church figure who, on reaching experience thresholds, raises the hero's Rank and grants Mantras — the passwords that store rank, gear, and the furthest church reached

**what —** the church figure who, on reaching experience thresholds, raises the hero's Rank and grants Mantras — the passwords that store rank, gear, and the furthest church reached

**where —** FAX · Faxanadu — Hudson Soft, NES 1989 (Famicom 1987; Falcom's Xanadu line)  Framework inputs: Faxanadu; the World Tree; Eolis; the Mantras; the card-keys; Golds & Ranks  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** He is the keeper of the save and the soul of progress: the one who turns experience into a title and a word you can carry back from death.

**how —** Crystallized from Faxanadu (NES 1989) — Famicom Xanadu, on Falcom's licensed Xanadu name.

**◌ the mythos —** He is the keeper of the save and the soul of progress: the one who turns experience into a title and a word you can carry back from death. a being of the World Tree and the climb to the Evil One

